article.description: Elijah Olaniyi had 20 points as Stony Brook beat Norfolk State 81-65 on Sunday.
article.headline: Olaniyi lifts Stony Brook past Norfolk St. 81-65
article.linkText: Olaniyi lifts Stony Brook past Norfolk St. 81-65
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Elijah Olaniyi had 20 points as Stony Brook beat Norfolk State 81-65 on Sunday. Olaniyi shot 8 for 10 from the foul line. He added seven rebounds and seven assists. Andrew Garcia had 18 points and eight rebounds for Stony Brook (9-6), which earned its fourth straight home victory. Makale Foreman added 16 points. Miles Latimer had 11 points for the home team. Norfolk State totaled 17 first-half points, a season low for the team. Joe Bryant Jr. had 18 points for the Spartans (4-11). Jermaine Bishop added 17 points. Steven Whitley had 14 points, 10 rebounds and eight assists. Stony Brook plays Maine on the road next Sunday. Norfolk State plays Bethune-Cookman at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
